			   <div class="col-sm-8">
				   <h2>Input Groups</h2> 
				   <p>The <code>.input-group</code> class is a container to enhance an input by adding an icon, text or a button 
				       in front or behind it as a  <em>"help text"</em>.</p>
					<p>The <code>.input-group-addon</code> class attaches an icon or help text next to the input field.</p>
				      <form action="#" >
					       <div class="input-group">
							   <span class="input-group-addon"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></i></span>
							   <input class="form-control" id="user" type="text" name="user" placeholder="Enter username">
						   </div>
					        <div class="input-group">
								<span class="input-group-addon"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-lock"></i></span>
								<input class="form-control" id="pass" name="password" type="password" placeholder="Enter password">
							</div>
							<div class="input-group">
								<span class="input-group-addon">Birthplace</span>
								<input class="form-control" id="birth" name="birthplace" type="text" placeholder="Where were you born?">
							</div>
					  </form>
				   <p>It can also be used on the right side of the input:</p>
				    <div class="input-group">
						<input class="form-control" id="phone" name="telephone" type="tel" placeholder="Enter your telephone number">
						<span class="input-group-addon"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-phone"></i></span>
					</div>
				   <h2>Input Group Buttons</h2>
				   <p>The <code>.input-group</code> class is a container to enhance an input by adding an icon, text or a button in
        				   front or behind it as a <em>"help desk"</em>.</p>
				   <p>The <code>.input-group-btn</code> class attaches a button next to an input field. This is often used as a search bar.</p>
				    <form>
					    <div class="input-group">
							<input class="form-control" id="search" type="search" name="search" placeholder="Enter search query...">
							<div class="input-group-btn">
								<button class="btn btn-success"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-search"></i></button>
							</div>
						</div>
					
					</form>
			   </div>
		   </div>
	   </div>
     
